  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Namibia Drought 2013</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A national state of emergency was declared by the Government of Namibia in May 2013 requesting international assistance for an estimated 331 000 people in rural communities classified as food insecure (14% of the total population). Another 450 000 were classed as moderately food insecure and the results of an Inter-Agency Emergency Food Security Assessment indicated that upcoming agricultural production will be poor and exacerbate these issues due to the lowest seasonal rainfall for decades. The Namibia Red Cross Society (NRCS) launched an appeal to intervene in four of the worst affected regions.</narrative>
  </description>
